1:
Praise Yahweh.
\q Praise Yahweh, my soul.
\q
2:
I give praise to Yahweh with all my life;
\q I will sing praises to my God as long as I exist.
3:
Do not put your trust in princes
\q or in mankind, in whom there is no salvation.
\q
4:
When a person's life's breath stops, he returns to the ground;
\q on that day his plans end.
5:
Blessed is he who has the God of Jacob for his help,
\q whose hope is in Yahweh his God.
\q
7:
He executes justice for the oppressed
\q and gives food to the hungry.
\q Yahweh frees the prisoners;
\q
9:
Yahweh protects the foreigners in the land;
\q he lifts up the fatherless and widow,
\q but he opposes the wicked.
\q
10:
Yahweh will reign forever,
\q your God, Zion, for all generations.
\q Praise Yahweh.
